JD Malat Gallery @jdmalatgallery is thrilled to announce an exclusive collaboration with the iconic British brand Aspinal of London. Aspinal have created a collection of limited-edition silk scarves, taking creative inspiration from Kojo Marfo’s innovative compositions featuring abstract figures, animals and vibrant floral designs. 

Kojo’s work is truly unique and I am so pleased that Aspinal and Kojo have come together for this collaboration. Aspinal is classic, elegant and timeless. Kojo’s work is innovative and culturally connective. Bringing the two together is really rewarding as it marks an unexpected fusion of two seemingly very different art forms. I think it is important, now more than ever, to challenge the status quo and do something different because that is what encourages change and development.

node.text:
‘Physis’, by Spanish artist Luis Olaso is officially open @jdmalatgallery in London Mayfair 

Having exhibited in leading cultural hubs such as Spain, Finland, Japan, Portugal and the United States, Olaso is renowned for his expressive canvases depicting abstracted still-lifes. The paintings in ‘Physis’ reference Olaso’s fondness for nature and his lived environment; he states his home is filled with plants, resembling a “jungle”. The influence of his home over his work is apparent when looking at the refined forms of glasses and vases in ‘Composition for a Saturday's night dinner'.

While it is natural to draw parallels between the ensembles of objects in Olaso’s work and the mimetic tradition of still-life painting, Olaso contrastingly seeks to move his painting away from an illustrative function and instead present an abstraction of forms based on his feelings, state of mind, and personal views.
